other_tests.findings: Marked hypoplasia of the optic nerves bilaterally and the absence of septum pellucidum.

WISC-V performance placed him in the average range of intelligence with scatter among scores and particular weakness in processing speed. The Woodcock-Johnson IV Tests of Cognitive Abilities showed short-term working memory in the average range, long-term working memory in the low average range, auditory processing in the average range, and cognitive efficiency in the low range. No sign of a specific learning disability was noted from the Woodcock-Johnson IV Tests of Achievements.
